        public static final edu.umass.cs.gnsserver.gnsapp.packet.InternalCommandPacket fieldRead(java.lang.String targetGUID,
                                                                                         java.lang.String field,
                                                                                         edu.umass.cs.gnsserver.interfaces.InternalRequestHeader header)
                                                                                  throws org.json.JSONException,
                                                                                         InternalRequestException
        Identical to GNSCommand.fieldReadArray(String, String, GuidEntry) except that the last querierGUID argument is replaced by an internal request header. For internal operations, we need the GNSProtocol.ORIGINATING_GUID to perform ACL checks or to "charge" it an operation (for accounting purposes) but we don't need to generate or verify its signatures. This and other information is in InternalRequestHeader.
